FAQ

How does a voice AI agent handle a customer interrupting it?
Modern enterprise voice AI agents use advanced "barge-in" technology. This allows the AI to immediately stop speaking when the customer interrupts, process the new information, and dynamically adjust its response, just like a natural human conversation.

Can a voice AI agent securely update records in Salesforce?
Yes. Enterprise-grade AI agents use secure, authenticated API connections to safely push and pull data from Salesforce in real time, securely updating fields, creating logs, and triggering workflows without manual entry.

What happens if the AI cannot solve the customer's problem?
When an AI encounters a complex issue or a frustrated caller, it initiates an intelligent human handoff. It transfers the call to the appropriate live agent, instantly passing along the complete call transcript and CRM context so the customer doesn't have to repeat their issue.

How long does it typically take to deploy a voice AI agent?
While simple FAQ bots can be deployed in days, enterprise-level deployments with deep CRM and Zendesk integrations typically follow a phased approach over a few weeks. This includes designing dialogue flows, connecting APIs, and conducting rigorous internal testing.

Is voice AI technology only suitable for English-speaking customers?
No. Leading platforms offer multilingual support. Advanced voice AI agents can converse fluently in over 50 languages and various regional accents, often featuring real-time language detection to switch languages based on the caller's preference.

